132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 233
H.P. 156 House of Representatives, January 21, 2025
An Act to Prohibit Biological Males from Participating in School
Athletic Programs and Activities Designated for Females When
State Funding Is Provided to the School
Reference to the Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CAMPBELL of Orrington.
Cosponsored by Senator HAGGAN of Penobscot and
Representatives: COLLINS of Sidney, GREENWOOD of Wales, HAGGAN of Hampden,
RUDNICKI of Fairfield, SOBOLESKI of Phillips, STROUT of Harrington, THORNE of
Carmel, UNDERWOOD of Presque Isle.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §14 is enacted to read:
3 §14. Biological males' participation in female athletic programs and activities at
4 schools that receive state funding
5 A school administrative unit or an elementary school, secondary school or
6 postsecondary educational institution in the State that receives any state funding may not
7 allow a person whose biological sex assigned at birth is male to participate in an athletic
8 program or activity that is designated for females.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill prohibits a school administrative unit or an elementary school, secondary
1111 school or postsecondary educational institution in the State that receives any state funding
1122 from allowing a person whose biological sex assigned at birth is male to participate in an
1133 athletic program or activity that is designated for females.
